<P>A VIEVV OF THE Engli&s;h Acqui&s;itions IN GUINEA, AND THE <HI>Ea&s;t-Indies,</HI> WITH An Account of the Religion, Govern|ment, Wars, &s;trange Cu&s;toms, Bea&s;ts, Serpents, Mon&s;ters, and other Ob&s;er|vables in tho&s;e Countries.</P>
<P>Together with A De&s;cription of the I&s;le of St. <HI>Helena;</HI> And the Bay of <HI>Sculdania,</HI> where the <HI>Engli&s;h</HI> u&s;u|ally refre&s;h in their Voyages to the <HI>Indies.</HI></P>
<P><HI>Intermixt with plea&s;ant Relations, and Enlivened with Picture.</HI></P>
<P>By <HI>R. B.</HI> Author of the <HI>Engli&s;h Empire</HI> in <HI>America, Englands Monarchs,</HI> and the <HI>Hi|&s;tory of</HI> Scotland <HI>and</HI> Ireland, &amp;c.</P>
<P><HI>LONDON,</HI> Printed for <HI>Nath. Crouch</HI> at the <HI>Bell</HI> in the <HI>Poultrey</HI> near <HI>Cheap&s;ide.</HI> 1686.</P>
